---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" path="/about" pageWidth="wide" pageClass="pt-10">
  <article class="rm-prose max-w-[48rem]">
    <h1>About rightmodel</h1>
    <p>
      I built rightmodel because developers, including me, default to the biggest model too often.
      Renaming a variable gets the same model as designing a database schema. The waste is real, and
      the habit is hard to break without something that makes the right choice obvious.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm Regnard Raquedan, a Senior Solutions Architect at GitLab and a Google Developer Expert.
      I built this as a personal project on weekends. It is not a startup.
    </p>
    <p>
      rightmodel is free and intended to stay that way. No signups, no ads, no upsells. The
      classification logic is open source, so if a recommendation looks wrong, open an issue or send
      a pull request with a better signal pattern.
    </p>
    <p>
      Find me at <a href="https://regnard.raquedan.com">regnard.raquedan.com</a>, on
      <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/raquedan">LinkedIn</a>, or via my
      <a href="https://developers.google.com/community/experts/directory/profile/profile-regnard-raquedan">
        GDE profile
      </a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
